g.text: Inland Empire: It's not a ghost story. It's a curse -- and Garte ought be made knowledgeable so he can perform counter-spells.
Logic: This seems to be some kind of workshop. For fixing up pinball machines -- a long time ago. Everything is covered with dust now...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Looks like it. I'm guessing Martinaise North 22 used to be a pinball arcade before it became a hostel. There are machines left over..." He taps his foot.
You: "Looks like they gave up on fixing the pinball machines at some point."
Looks like they gave up on fixing the pinball machines at some point.
You: "Whirling-in-Rags was once the East Delta Pinball arcade. This is all left over from that."
Logic: Yes. Martinaise North 22 used to be a pinball arcade.
Logic: Yes. Pinball hasn't enjoyed a heyday for fifteen or twenty years.
You: "Could this mean the Whirling-in-Rags really *is* part of the Doomed Commercial Area?"
"Could this mean the Whirling-in-Rags really *is* part of the Doomed Commercial Area?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Ah, yes -- as the novelty dicemaker said." He makes a note in his notebook. "This has absolutely nothing to do with the case, I'm sure. But I do like a nice little *connection*."
Logic: Yes. It would mean that.
Logic: And it has been forgotten. Now, there is only one working machine in the main hall -- the rest is lost to dust.
Logic: As the Dicemaker said, yes; it all fits. Not that it has anything to do with the case, but it is a nice connection!
You: "Doesn't look like that pinball machine will ever get fixed."
Doesn't look like that pinball machine will ever get fixed.
Reaction Speed: Remember the *Dicemaker*?! Then that means...
Logic: So this is where they brought faulty pinball machines to fix them up -- a long time ago. Everything is covered with dust now...
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant looks around the dusty, crowded room, inspecting the tools on the shelf.
Kim Kitsuragi: "He does not appear to be the kind of man who likes his establishment to be part of a neighbourhood ghost story. About *bankruptcy*."
Perception (Hearing): A creak, some dust falls off a shelf.
Kim Kitsuragi: "If that's true then our *cafeteria manager* is not going to like it." He looks around. "We should tell him what we found up here -- *omitting* that suspicion."
Logic: And Garte would not like that. He should probably be made aware that his establishment is part of the neighbourhood ghost story.
Logic: Stupid superstition. But still -- it would be *interesting* to see what the cafeteria manager thinks of this...
You: "This used to be a... pinball workshop."
This used to be a... pinball workshop.
Inland Empire: But then it went bankrupt... your skin crawls from making the connection!
Kim Kitsuragi: "At some point -- twenty years ago? Fifteen maybe. Before pinball went out of vogue."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Downstairs in the hall -- next to the main door. One of them even works. I've seen one of the Hardies bang away at it."
